external_knowledge:
- "attended more than two training sessions" means the member has participated in more than two distinct training sessions;
- "made significant contributions to the community through generous payments" means the member has paid a total amount greater than 1000;
- "active engagement with newsletters" means the member has more than one newsletter subscription;
- "the most recent member to join" means the member with the latest joining date.

- Active members are those whose `is_active` status is 1;
- The total payment for 2022 is calculated by summing payments made in that year;
- If a member has no payments in 2022, the total payment is shown as 0.

- 'Premium' membership level indicates a higher-tier membership;
- 'Total payment' refers to the sum of all payments made by the member;
- 'Training sessions' are specific events attended by members for training purposes.

- "training hours" refer to the total duration of training programs a member has completed;
- "membership level" and "specialization" are attributes that describe the member's status and expertise;
- "detailed membership descriptions" include the name and description of the membership level.

- "Training sessions" refer to the sessions members attend as part of their membership;
- "Cumulative payment" is the sum of all payments made by members, calculated within each membership level;
- "Highest cumulative payment" represents the maximum value of the cumulative payments across all members.

- 'Premium' members are those with a higher membership level, typically associated with more benefits or higher fees;
- 'Total payment amount' refers to the cumulative amount of money a member has paid for their membership or services;
- 'Training sessions attended' refers to the number of training sessions a member has participated in.

- A 'completed training session' means the training_status is 'Completed';
- 'Contributed to the garden of knowledge' refers to the total_amount_paid;
- 'Blossomed through more than one completed training session' means the member has completed more than one training session.

- "Active members" are those whose `is_active` flag is set to 1;
- "Completed training sessions" refers to training sessions where `training_status` is 'Completed';
- "Top three membership levels" are the membership levels with the highest number of active members who have completed training sessions.

- 'Certified Professional' is a specific certification that members can hold;
- 'Lapse' refers to the certification being past its expiry date;
- 'Not renewed' refers to the membership being inactive and past the renewal date.
